    "Lastly, the coefficient of variation is a statistical metric that is often used to evaluate the relative variability or dispersion of data.",
    "It is calculated as the ratio of a dataset's standard deviation to its mean, presented as a percentage 53.",
    "The statistical analysis was done in RStudio (Version 2024.04.02+764, R Version 4.4.0).",
